The prominent figures in the local government are listed below. The royal vault contents are also listed.
ARCHDUKE: [Level 17 Warrior] Lippard: [HGT: 5ft, 1in; WGT: 150 lbs] He is a old male human that is ragged in appearance. He has curly, white hair.  He is generally trusting, but also diplomatic. His disposition is even tempered but he is vengeful by nature. He is quite brave in the face of danger. He can be perceived as amoral when it comes to his morality. He has a great interest in legends.  DRESSED IN: brown boots, tan long pants, yellowish-green skullcap, and a light-purple doublet. POSSESSIONS: fake treasure map, small silver holy symbol, sling (3 stones). ARMS & ARMOR: crossbow (1d4+1 damage) with about 11 bolts each, ring mail armor, kite shield
ARCHDUCHESS: [Level 7 Rogue] Freth: [HGT: 6ft, 9in; WGT: 280 lbs] She is a mature female human that is dirty in appearance. She has short, blonde hair.  She is generally perceptive, but also modest. Her disposition is insensitive but she is forgiving by nature. She is quite cowardly in the face of danger. she comes off as being quite motivated. She can be perceived as normal when it comes to her morality. She has a great interest in fishing.  DRESSED IN: dark-red thigh boots, a dark-brown belt with a gold buckle, blue robe, and a purple plain dress. POSSESSIONS: jerky (4 ea), club. ARMS & ARMOR: hand axe (1d6 damage), cloth armor, buckler
ROYAL VAULT: JEWELRY: Silver 2 Inch Square Pyramid (280gp) --- GEMS [3 each]: Golden Yellow Topaz (93gp) --- Scroll with the lowest level magic-user spell --- GEMS [2 each]: Hematite (9gp) --- GEMS [2 each]: Sard Quartz (29gp) --- Bow +2 [magically carved of oak] --- Legendary Trident of Adenthimor the Bandit - trident +1 [the fork is made of mithril and has a bone handle...the name of Adenthimor is engraved on the fork] --- GEMS [2 each]: Deep Blue Spinel (103gp) --- GEMS [2 each]: Golden Pearl (77gp) --- JEWELRY: Silver Clasp (304gp) --- Rare Ring of Morturus - ring of influence [a bone ring with a lapis lazuli set in it...the command word to use this is `ehnojogh`, which can be learned with identifying magic - it has 48 charges] --- JEWELRY: Golden Arm-ring (1,024gp) --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gemmed Buckle (1,056gp) --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gold Arm-ring (708gp) --- GEMS [2 each]: Obsidian (4gp) --- GEMS [1 each]: Banded Agate (3gp) --- Mattrick`s Helm {this platinum helm has a wolf symbol on the sides and allows the wearer to make a magical attack with their mind causing 4d4 damage once per day} --- JEWELRY: Golden Gemmed Bracelet (3,180gp) --- GEMS [2 each]: Bloodstone (22gp) --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gemmed Bracelet (900gp) --- GEMS [2 each]: Tiger Eye (2gp) --- JEWELRY: Golden Clasp (182gp) --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gemmed Broach (405gp) --- JEWELRY: Silver Goblet (272gp) --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gemmed Coronet (1,095gp) --- Zases` Astonishing Floppy Hat {this red floppy hat allows the wearer to make a magical attack with their mind causing 4d8 damage once per day} --- JEWELRY: Silvery Gold Arm-ring (985gp) --- A BROWN LEATHER SATCHEL CONTAINING: 90,000cp

Merchants are displayed in what building they are in.  There is also an owner along with a possible list of items one may obtain from them.  Merchants will indicate how much gold is stored somewhere in the vicinity.  This gold can be referenced for possible theft, or simply how much they can possibly negotiate with if characters attempt to sell items.   Some items have an "In Stock" value.  This number is how many, of that item, the merchant will have restocked every month.  If only "3" of an item are available, and the characters buy all "3", then the merchant will not get another "3" until the next month.
